in the st century  see also  references  further reading  external links backgroundedit the company was started by franklin w olin in east alton illinois as the equitable powder company olin created the company for the purpose of supplying the areas coal mines and limestone quarries with explosives olins blasting and gunpowder company expanded into the production of cartridges in  historyedit a family has lunch in lake charles louisiana on the beach opposite the olin mathieson chemical plant  expansion and acquisitionsedit franklin olin along with his two sons john and spencer formed the western cartridge company in direct competition with remington and winchester for a time his competitors were able to get their suppliers to shut off sources of raw materials in an attempt to drive olin out of business in order to survive olin diversified the activities of the company the company bought a paper manufacturer the ecusta paper company in pisgah forest north carolina a lead shot facility an explosive primer facility a cartridge brass manufacturing facility and a fiber wad facility the company also started its own brass mill together these companies became the western cartridge company through it the olins made a fortune supplying ammunition during world war i in  western bought the winchester company olin merged the two in  forming winchesterwestern in  the various olin companies were organized under a new corporate parent olin industries inc at the time olin industries and its subsidiary companies ran the st louis arsenal and contributed to the war effort with manufacturing roles at the badger army ammunition and lake city army ammunition plants olins new haven and east alton plants employed about  workers each—producing the guns and smallcaliber ammunition needed during world war ii the war production helped the olins to become one of the wealthiest american families of the time after the war the olins acquired the mathieson chemical corporationalso founded in  unrelated then to olin mathieson alkali works began business in saltville va and in  acquired its neighbor the holston salt and plaster corp saltville then became a quintessential company town in saltville it produced chlorine and caustic soda leaching a considerable amount of methylmercury by the companys own estimates up to  pounds per day into the soils and the north fork of the holston river this site was declared a superfund site in  in  the mathieson chemical company as it was known by then acquired the pharmaceutical firm of er squibb  sons spun off in  and is now part of bristolmyers squibb in  mathieson bought a controlling interest in the pharmaceutical firm of e r squibb  sons now part of bristolmyers squibb afterward the corporation diversified its interests into a wide variety of businesses including plastics cellophane bauxite mining automotive specialties ramset nailing tools and home construction the olin ski company manufactured camping and skiing gear olin skis are now produced under a licensing agreement by k sports in the s and s the company used this bird logo and later the slogan the rare bird in the business olin industries and mathieson chemical merged in  to form the olin mathieson chemical corporation the new company had  employees  domestic and  foreign plants the company manufactured phenoxy herbicides and anticrop agents for fort detrick under contract to the us army chemical corps john olin retired in  the following year the company brought in hardware experienced executives to run winchester the new management team introduced cheap forgedmetal parts into the winchester line which eventually damaged the quality reputation winchester had previously enjoyed  muck dam collapseedit nearly  years prior to olin acquiring mathieson chemical a muck dam collapsed sending a foot wall of water mud mercury and alkali down the holston river valley into the company town of henrytown a community of saltville va bodies homes and cars were washed as far as seven miles down the valley in the aftermath of the flood  people had died one was missing and as many as  were injured corporate reductionedit the company became the olin corporation in  and began to sell off many of its acquired businesses since then the olin corporation has been shrinking except for brief expansion in the early s in addition to the above mentioned olin corporation was the first us corporation to be prosecuted for violations of the arms embargo and eventually was convicted in the early  for selling winchester rifles to private dealers in the south africa when charged the winchester division of the olin corporation affirmed in a legal brief that the winchester employees principally responsible for dealing with the state department on export license matters over the years developed the belief that the department was winking” at the representation by the company that arms sent to south africa were said to be destined for other countries — “memorandum on behalf of olin corporation brief filed in us district court new haven conn  march  after ongoing declines in its business at winchester on december   olin made the decision to sell winchester firearms to the firms employees under the name us repeating arms company olin however kept the winchester brand name and licensed it to us repeating arms company olin sold its european winchester ammunition business and also licensed the winchester brand name to giat of versailles france olin spun off its specialty chemicals business on february   as arch chemicals inc it now focuses more on its ammunition brass and chloralkali businesses olin is the third largest chloralkali producer in the usa olin announced the sale of its brass division in october  losing  million in the sale olin brass is now owned by global brass in the st centuryedit the ammunition business was and is strong due to the iraq and afghanistan wars since  the olin corporation has been moving some manufacturing of its winchester products from east alton to oxford mississippi which started with the rimfire cartridge lr production then its load and pack operations in  the company announced the move of centerfire manufacturing to oxford mississippi a maintenance building at the winchester ammunition plant in an isolated area of east alton burned and was a total loss on sunday february   the cause is under investigation but no one was killed or injured seven area fire departments assisted in the response but encountered heavy smoke and fire according to east alton fire chief randy nelson on march   dow chemical company announced that it would spin off its chlorine and epoxy businesses and merge them with the olin corporation in a deal that would give dow control of the olin corporation on october   olin successfully acquired the dow’s us gulf coast chloralkali and vinyl global chlorinated organics and global epoxy business units in addition to  percent interest in the dow mitsui chloralkali joint venture  see alsoedit missouri portal companies portal f w olin foundation john m olin foundation referencesedit  ecusta epa webpage retrieved   olins history olin corporation online retrieved may    roanoke times article accessed   us epa superfund site  va department environmental quality  brown megan e and kowalewski michal do local extinctions correlate with taphonomic signatures of freshwater mussel shells in the north fork holston river virginia paper no  presented at the  seattle annual meeting of the geological society of america  test wells to monitor ground water at olin superfund site near saltville va epa environmental news october    roanoke times article on dam  us epa superfund site  va department environmental quality   broad based flexibility business plan of john m olin retrieved   httpswwwnytimescombusinessadeftskimakerworksaslipperyslopehtml  rocky mountain arsenal summary of major events and problems  p  hawks chuck the winchester model  quote  was a big year for olinwinchester that was the year that their revised for cheaper manufacture line of firearms was introduced the reaction from gun writers and the shooting public to the changes was swift and terrible and winchester has never regained its former position of dominance  httpwwwgendisasterscomvirginiasaltvillevadambreakflooddecpage  article retrieved   washington notes on africa p  quotation olin corporation the first us corporation to be prosecuted for violations of the arms embargo was convicted for selling winchester rifles to private dealers in south africa  as cited in the cascade of arms managing conventional weapons proliferation p   out with a bang the loss of the classic winchester is loaded with symbolism january   article washington post retrieved november   article product guide winchester online retrieved   isle of capri will move hq to creve coeur january   article by van der werf martin st louis postdispatch third edition business p a retrieved august    winchester ec next online retrieved   winchester ammunition considering full move to mississippi wordpress online august    httpwwwpjstarcomarticlenews  david gelles dow chemical to merge unit with olin new york times march   further readingedit winchester an american legend by wilson r l random house  external linksedit olin corporation home page olin brass olin chloralkali products retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleolincorporationoldid categories olin corporationcompanies listed on the new york stock exchangeammunition manufacturerschemical companies of the united statescompanies based in st louis county missouricompanies established in smyth county virginiaski equipment manufacturerssuperfund sites in alabamahidden categories pages using deprecated image syntax navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store int